<div class="testimonials-pagecontent"><h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
<p>When you register on our website, you must enter a minimum of the following information: First Name, Last Name (Surname), Email Address and Country.</p>
<p>Your information helps us to better meet your individual needs and helps to maximise the security of any monies or documentation sent to you. It also helps us respond more effectively to any questions and correspondence we receive from you.</p>
<p>We are continually making improvements to our website based on information and feedback we receive from you.</p>
<p><strong>How do we protect your information?</strong></p>
<p>A set of security measures to maintain the security of your personal information is implemented at all times.</p>
<p>We offer the use of a firewall.  All personal and financial data provides that information be transmitted using Secure Socket Layer (SSL) technology and then encrypted into our databases for entry of payments, which can only be accessed by our admin and personnel who maintain our protected and secure information.</p>
<p><strong>Are cookies used?</strong></p>
<p>Yes, cookies are tiny files that the website or its service provider transfers to the hard drive of your computer through your browser (if allowed), which allow the website to recognize your browser and remember certain information. We use cookies to process data of purchases made by you and our other members.  It also helps us understand and save your preferences for future purchases, keep track of advertisements and compile aggregate data about the traffic and interaction with the web so we can offer more accurate and better tools to enhance your future CT experiences.</p>
<p><strong>Do we disclose the information to third parties?</strong></p>
<p>NO, we do not sell, trade or transfer personal information to any third parties.
In addition, we will only disclose information when we feel it necessary to fulfil the requirements of the law, enforce our website policies, or protect the rights, property and safety of all of our members.</p>
<p>On occasion, we may include or offer third party products or services on our website.</p>
<p>Our users and advertisers also show content and links to third party websites, included in the services purchased on our website.
These other third party websites may have separate privacy policies, so please be aware that we do not endorse or assume responsibility or liability for the content or activities of any third party websites. </p>
<p><strong>Children's Online Privacy Protection Act Compliance (Child Protection Act US online)</strong><br />
We are complying with the requirements of COPPA (Children's Online Privacy Protection Act), so that we do not collect information from children under 18 years of age. Our website, products and services are aimed at people aged 18 years or older.
Read our Terms and Conditions below, in which the use of the CT website is established, the disclaimers and limitations of liability based on the use of this CT website.<br />
By your use our CT website, you hereby consent to our Privacy Policy.</p>
<p><strong>Changes in our Privacy Policy</strong><br />
At any point, moment or time, we may decide to change our Privacy Policy, and we will post the changes on this page</p>
<p><strong>Contact us</strong><br />
If you are in doubt regarding the Privacy Policy, contact us through Support.</p></div>
